		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Homebrew isn't too bad, in terms of building the carts. If you have basic electronics knowledge and have been taught a bit about how static ram and EPROMs work, then its just a matter of finding the pinouts, wiring the socket, then burn the chips and away you go.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
