	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Of those 700 famicom games that are not released, about 125 have been translated to English.  About half are decent translations (the other are work in progress).  Even less can be put onto north american carts; there's a lot more boards in the japan that were never make/sold here.  So these games can't be made!
<br />
<br />Lastly, lets face it.  As a collector, the great thing about these things in the cart labels!  
<br />
<br />By the end of the day, of the 700 famicom games out there, only a handful have nice pintable labels, perfect english translations and can be put back on a cart.
<br />
<br />If you do plan on doing it on your own.  There's lots of resources here to show you how to do it.  The most important thing, as with everything in life, is to invest $$$ in good tools.
<br />
<br />Good luck!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


